&lt;p&gt;Community Staff Nurse – District Nursing Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Description&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the District Nursing Service; we are&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;seeking to appoint highly enthusiastic and motivated individuals to join the&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;service as a Community Staff Nurse - the post is fixed term for 12 months. We&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;are looking for enthusiastic nurses who are interested in caring for patients in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;their home environment. Successful applicants would be required to work&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;independently and as part of a team and will be responsible for the provision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;of evidence based treatment interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operational hours of the service are 24 hours a day 7 days per week 365&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;days per year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amongst your repertoire of skills, the following will be essential:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Registered General Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Excellent communication and caring skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Excellent time management and organizational skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;You will be expected to be flexible to meet service need&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stacey Batty, Lead Nurse at stacey.batty@lscft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel No: 07580180046&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katherine Jones - Interim Service - Manager -7773947530&lt;/p&gt;
